The paper proposes a deep neural network model for human activity recognition, which involves learning from sensor data. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and computer vision, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The use of residual networks and the focus on improving accuracy suggest that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most likely category. The use of sensor data and wearable datasets also suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of deep neural networks and the focus on optimization suggest that the paper could also be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the focus on practical applications suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
